This paper discusses the security of password-secured systems and the design of better security protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses a simplified model to analyze distributed attacks, which involves optimization and probability theory, indicating that it could also belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of botnets and the analysis of their impact on computational effort suggest that the paper could also be classified under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
